But notice

>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exhaust_gas_recirculation

which sez

Although EGR does measurably slow combustion, this can largely be 
compensated for by advancing spark timing.


Second point:-

>http://my350z.com/forum/engine-drivetrain-and-forced-induction-diy/428669-diy-how-to-build-an-electronic-stethoscope-electronic-det-can.html

	If you can acquire a 'real' stethoscope, try that first. 
Versions for mechanics are sold; also some rtd medico may let you 
have one.  They are wonderful.  You can even get a fair idea of 
which  bearing is knocking  ...


